author: Jenel Few
title: Savannah's Woodville-Tompkins awarded for Go Build Georgia efforts
text:
Photos By Jenel Few Woodville-Tompkins Technical and Career High School was presented with a commendation from Governor Nathan Deal Tuesday during the Career, Technical, and Agricultural Education Regional meeting at Beach High School.
Woodville-Tompkins was recognized for achieving a Gold Designation with Go Build Georgia.
Go Build Georgia is a public/private partnership working with the Governor’s Office of Workforce Development. The program’s goal is to funnel students into skilled trades. Woodville-Tompkins participated in the Go Build Georgia Teams process last year.
